==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syle
<hw>Syle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sile</er> a
young herring.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A young herring
(<spn>Clupea harengus</spn>).</def> <altsp>[Also written
<asp>sile</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But our folk call them <qex>syle</qex>, and nought but
<qex>syle</qex>,⟦br⟧
And when they're grown, why then we call them herring.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Ingelow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

